THOUGHT: The crash occurs in SLPVectorizer's HorizontalReduction when generating keys for loads; it calls getUnderlyingObject on a pointer operand that can be null (e.g., load from null or GEP on null in the reproducer). Some path doesn't guard against a null underlying object, leading to dereferencing a null Value and crashing at Value::getType. I will inspect the SLPVectorizer.cpp around generateKeySubkey and HorizontalReduction::matchAssociativeReduction to add a null-check for the pointer operand/underlying object before hashing, defaulting to a safe key when it's null.

```bash
nl -ba llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp | sed -n '7080,7095p'; sed -n '18610,18690p' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && sed -n '1,120p' llvm/lib/Analysis/ValueTracking.cpp && grep -n "generateKeySubkey" -n llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && python3 - <<'PY'
import re,sys
path="llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp"
s=open(path).read()
# Patch: wrap uses of getUnderlyingObject/LI->getPointerOperand in generateKeySubkey caller to handle null
patched=s
# Add a helper to safely get underlying object hash key when pointer may be null
if "SafeUnderlyingObjectKey" not in s:
    insert_at = s.find("static hash_code generateKey(")
    helper = """
static Optional<hash_code> SafeUnderlyingObjectKey(Value *V, const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI) {
  if (!V) return None;
  // Limit recursion like getUnderlyingObject does.
  Value *UO = getUnderlyingObject(V, 6);
  if (!UO) return None;
  // Some constant null pointers can appear; treat them uniformly.
  if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(UO)) return Optional<hash_code>(hash_value(0u));
  // For undef, also provide a stable key.
  if (isa<UndefValue>(UO)) return Optional<hash_code>(hash_value(1u));
  return Optional<hash_code>(hash_value(UO));
}
"""
    patched = patched[:insert_at] + helper + patched[insert_at:]
# In HorizontalReduction::matchAssociativeReduction lambda, locate generateKeySubkey usage
patched = re.sub(r'(generateKeySubkey\(\s*LI->getPointerOperand\(\)\s*,\s*TLI\s*,\s*SubkeyGen\s*,\s*[^)]*\))',
                 r'( [&](){ auto sk = SafeUnderlyingObjectKey(LI->getPointerOperand(), TLI); return sk ? *sk : hash_value(2u);}() )',
                 patched)
open(path,"w").write(patched)
print("Patched SLPVectorizer.cpp")
PY
 && ninja -C build/llvm-build/111887 && cat /tmp/test.ll | build/llvm-build/111887/bin/opt -S --passes=slp-vectorizer -mtriple=riscv64-unknown-linux-gnu -mattr=+v - 2>&1 | tee /tmp/opt_out.txt && submit-patch
```

